{"tid":2090353,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"英國人：750萬香港人喺一夜之間失去民主","createTime":"2020-07-02T06:23:09.000Z","updateTime":"2020-07-02T09:04:53.000Z","uid":52429,"like":32,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"deff54e2e8b1f27cc28bad148d5a0368c007bd25","tid":2090353,"uid":52429,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-07-02T06:23:09.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/QszsU3L.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FQszsU3L.jpg&h=778ab5a7&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nOvernight 7.5 million people in Hong Kong lost their democracy. Their right to protest. Their right to freedom of speech. Their right to the rule of law. Their right to an independent judiciary.<br />\n<br />\nOvernight 7.5 million people are now under the complete control of a totalitarian Communist regime in Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nOvernight China have violated the Sino-British Joint Declaration guaranteeing the freedoms and civil liberties of Hong Kong post the 1997 handover.<br />\n<br />\nOur government in the UK has done nothing and said nothing other than offer refuge for people to leave their home, in another act of shame against our former territory. 350,000 people in Hong Kong hold British passports. We owe it to them and to the people of Hong Kong to stand up for their freedoms and rights, when the red darkness has all but extinguished theirs.<br />\n<br />\nIts time for this country to make a stand against China.<br />\nIts time to stand up and fight for the principles we all hold and value dearly.<br />\nIts time to stand up for the people of Hong Kong.<br />\n<br />\nTo the people of Hong Kong a message, 'The UK has not forgotten you'. 🇬🇧<br />\n<br />\nPlease share this far and wide. Put pressure on the UK government to act.<br />\n<br />\nLink:<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/scott.pullen.587/posts/10221667125084058\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fscott.pullen.587%